      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the suggestion. the problem is we're working on bare-metal hardware for the most part, so i can't exactly run valgrind on the actual target controller during real-time operation. it's a pretty constrained environment.\n\ngiven that i can't rely on heavy profiling tools, what are some low-level ways to monitor heap usage or instrument the code to find these leaks manually? maybe some manual hooks or specific patterns i should look for in the allocator?",
